Setup
=====
Install required gems.

bundle install

Usage
=====

Add column of latitudes and longtitudes for addresses in a spreadsheet and generate a corresponding KML file.
  Usage: CSVtoKML.rb [options]
  
    -a ADDRESS_COLUMN_NAME,          Name of the column containing addresses.
 Default: Address
        --address-column-name
    -u UTL_COLUMN_NAME,              Name of the column containing the link/url.
 Default: href
        --link-column-name
    -b, --base-url BASE_URL          Base URL.
 Default: href
    -n NAME_COLUMN_NAME,             Name of the column containing name.
 Default: 0
        --name-column-name
    -d DESCRIPTION_COLUMN_NAME,      Name of the column containing description.
 Default: description
        --description_column_name
    -s SEPARATING_CHARACTER,         Separating character in the files.
 Default: tab
        --separating-character
    -f, --in-file IN_FILE            File to process.
 Default: Default.tsv
    -m, --map-name MAP_NAME          Name of the map.
 Default: Map
    -e, --engine-name ENGINE_NAME    Name of the geocoding engine eg google, yahoo.
 Default: nominatim
    -t TEXT_TO_ADD_TO_ADDRESS,       Text to add to addresses.
 Default: 
        --text-to-add
    -h, --help                       Display help functions.
